The paper deals with geometric spanners, which are a fundamental concept in computational geometry (cs.CG). It also involves the study of highly connected graphs, which is a topic in graph theory and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper uses mathematical analysis to prove lower bounds on the number of edges in robust spanners, which falls under numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also involves the construction of spanners, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the concept of robustness in spanners is related to the resilience of networks, which is a topic in social networks and information retrieval (cs.SI).
